    <h1>MorningGloryCupcake</h1>
<img src="images/20995-easy-morning-glory-muffins-DDMFS-4x3-7da085b1163d499eb655aeef1e07f9b3.webp" alt="MorningGloryCupcake">
<caption> MorningGloryCupcake </caption>
<h2><em>Description</em>
<p>
    I really enjoyed making these muffins. 
    I think this recipe is a brilliant mix of healthy and delicious! I made a few
    changes to the original recipe: I used 1 cup of honey instead of 1 1/2 cups of sugar,
    which made them nicely sweet without being overpowering. I also swapped the freshly grated 
    carrots for 2 cups of green vegetable pulp, which added a healthy twist. To spice things up,
    I added 1/4 teaspoon of ginger powder and 1/4 teaspoon of grated nutmeg.The mixed nuts—pecans, 
    walnuts, almonds, and Brazilian nuts—added a delicious crunch. Overall, these muffins were easy to
    make and turned out amazing! I’ll definitely be making them again.  
</p>
<h2><b>Ingredients</b><h2>
    <ul>
        <li>2 cups all-purpose flour</li>
        <li>1 1/4 cups white sugar </li>
        <li>2 teaspoons baking soda </li>
        <li>2 teaspoons ground cinnamon</li>
        <li>1/4 teaspoon salt</li>
        <li>2 cups shredded carrot</li>
        <li>1 apple-peeled,cored and shredded</li>
        <li>1/2 cup raisins</li>
        <li>1/2 cup chopped walnuts</li>
        <li>1/2 cup unsweetened flaked coconut</li>
        <li>3 large eggs</li>
        <li>1 cup vegetable oil</li>
        <li>2 Teaspoon vanilla extract</li>
    </ul>
<br>
<h2><b>steps</b></h2>
<ol>
    <li>
        Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 12-cup muffin tin or line cups with paper liners.
    </li>
    <li>  Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt together in a large bowl; stir in carrots, apple, raisins, walnuts, and coconut.
    </li>
    <li>Beat eggs, oil, and vanilla together in a separate bowl.
    </li>
    <li>Stir egg mixture into the carrot mixture until just moistened.
    </li>
    <li>Spoon batter into the prepared muffin cups, filling each 2/3 full.
    </li>
    <li>Bake in the preheated oven until tops spring back when lightly pressed, about 20 minutes. Cool in the tin for 5 minutes. Transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
    </li>
    <li>Enjoy!</li>
</ol>
